  "intent": "R-63: Design adversarial perimeter defence for the graph. Anyone with Neo4j write access can inject morpheme-labeled nodes via raw Cypher, bypassing all three enforcement layers. Injected nodes have no INSTANTIATES wiring, no CONTAINS placement, no observation recording — the governance layer is structurally blind. The fix must be structural enforcement at the database layer, NOT a periodic scan (compliance-as-monitoring anti-pattern). The design challenge: how does the database itself distinguish a governed write from an ungoverned write without creating a monitoring overlay? Explore Neo4j native capabilities: triggers, APOC callbacks, transaction metadata, property constraints, uniqueness constraints. Also explore cryptographic write tokens and append-only provenance chains. The solution must satisfy: (a) structural enforcement not detection, (b) no monitoring overlay, (c) works when the application layer is compromised. Reference: v5.0 Constitutional Coupling, A6 Minimal Authority, 10 compliance kills. Produce analysis and design options, not implementation code.",
